This paper discusses the training of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a popular topic in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper focuses on stabilization techniques for GAN training, which is a common issue in the field. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since GANs are a type of neural network, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, since the paper discusses the mathematical and theoretical aspects of GANs, cs.GR (Graphics) is also a possible sub-category.
